<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-08-01T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-08-01T12:00:00-05:00" n="491" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d491">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">560.AL/8–147: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Consul in Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Troutman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent niact</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-08-01T18:00:00+01:00">August 1,
                                1947—6 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>800. For Lovett and Nitze from Clayton. Absolutely essential I have authority
                        act wool tariff tomorrow morning as fear cannot hold Dominion Cabinet
                        members here longer. Have been trying telephone you all day to urge
                        Secretary himself go to President this afternoon, but line out of order. Am
                        still trying to phone. [Clayton.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Troutman</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>